<subSubSection id="04D9EFABD265F47EFF4CFADBFED4F8A9" pageId="1" pageNumber="145" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="4C7CBC20D265F47EFF4CFADBFEBEF98D" blockId="1.[151,1436,1368,1539]" pageId="1" pageNumber="145">
<emphasis id="7EB76032D265F47EFF4CFADBFEA1FAFD" bold="true" box="[151,276,1368,1394]" pageId="1" pageNumber="145">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Body form large to rather small. Head very large, upper half of head almost globular. Pronotum with parallel sides, somewhat widening in front. Male genitalia: hind margin of epiphallus with relatively long median projections, which is directed backwards. In this subgenus about 91 species occur worldwide; of these, 44 species have been reported from Asia-tropical, including the Indian subcontinent and the Indo-China region (
<bibRefCitation id="2852C1D1D265F47EFAC6FA47FF4AF98D" author="Cigliano, M. M. &amp; Braun, H. &amp; Eades, D. C. &amp; Otte, D." pageId="1" pageNumber="145" refId="ref5451" refString="Cigliano, M. M., Braun, H., Eades, D. C. &amp; Otte, D. (2022) Orthoptera Species File online. Version 5.0 / 5.0. Available from: http: // orthoptera. SpeciesFile. org (accessed 15 February 2022)" type="url" year="2022">
Cigliano 
<emphasis id="7EB76032D265F47EFA53FA46FF18F98D" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="145">et al</emphasis>
., 2022
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
